</svg></div></div><div class="c-line bio margin-40"></div><div class="t-rich-text w-richtext"><p>Phyo Aung Kyaw received a B.A. in Physics from Amherst College, and a Ph.D. in Engineering Sciences (Electrical Engineering) from the Thayer School of Engineering at Dartmouth College, where his research focused on improving the efficiency and compactness of next-generation higher-frequency power electronics. </p><p>Together with Aaron, he developed the first multi-layer self-resonant structure (MSRS) prototype, which is the cornerstone of Resonant Link’s wireless power system that won the 2017 APEC’s Best Paper Award. In 2021, Phyo was recognized as a Forbes 30 Under 30 for being one of the leading entrepreneurs working to change the world. </p><p>‍</p></div><div fs-mirrorclick-element="target" class="c-bio-close"><div class="c-bio-close-icon w-embed"><svg width="100%" viewBox="0 0 66 64" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
