</svg></div></div><div class="c-line bio margin-40"></div><div class="t-rich-text w-richtext"><p>Britt Tedeschi joined Resonant Link in early 2022 to lead its people function. Britt holds a B.A. in Psychology from the University of Miami and a MEd with a focus on adult learning and development from the University of Georgia. Britt has extensive experience developing, leading, and coaching high performing teams during periods of rapid change and high growth. </p><p>With a human-centric approach, Britt has scaled Resonant Link’s learning culture as the company has grown, centering transparency, inclusion, and belonging through defined career paths, remote-first practices, and intentional hiring processes. Britt lives in Rhode Island and is a frequent visitor at Resonant Link’s Vermont headquarters.</p></div><div fs-mirrorclick-element="target" class="c-bio-close"><div class="c-bio-close-icon w-embed"><svg width="100%" viewBox="0 0 66 64" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
